Ask HN: URL format for blog posts - which format is best?
text:
Example 1:

myblog.com/my-readeable-but-long-blog-post-title-in the-url

OR

myblog.com/posts/my-readeable-but-long-blog-post-title-in the-url

Example 2:

myblog.com/2022/08/my-readeable-but-long-blog-post-title-in the-url

Example 3:

myblog.com/62642060

---

Pro and cons:

Examples 1 and 2: Readable but long URLs. They may also help SEO (search engine optimisation).

Example 2: The date in the URL provide helpful context.

Example 3: A short URL easily shared (but URL is not descriptive).

Which of these URL formats do you prefer? Or do you think they don't really matter?

Thank you :-)

The opengauss active and standby architecture is used with keeplive
text:
Is there any risk in using opengauss active and standby architecture with keeplive?

Explanation: The use of the opengauss active/standby architecture with keeplive is mainly to consider that the application connection string does not need to be modified when the application uses the domain name (the domain name of the keeplive virtual IP) to connect and switch.

Is there a better architecture than this one for opengauss usage scenarios?
